"Pandora's Box"(1991)  
  Shit House Shuffle  
  *(Joe Perry)*  
  
  "At first I thought, who's gonna be interested in this, but then I  
  figured maybe someone will get something out of it"  
    -Joe Perry  
  
  *Here's my arrangement of this thirty-five second rock opera from*  
  *Pandora's Box. The main riff is also played in "South Station Blues" by the*  
  *Joe Perry Project. Have fun with it. Long live Aerosmith.*  
  *main riff:*  
  [E---------------------------------------------------------|  
  B---------------------------------------------------------|  
  G---------------------------------------------------------|  
  D-----------3p0---0---3p0---0-----0-----------------------|  
  A-----------------------------------------3-----2-----0---|  
  E---0h1\3-------------------------------------------------|]  
  *Play that riff moderately fast eight times and then try this:*  
    ***A   F#5  G5   A5  G5***  
  [E----------------------------------------------------------|  
  B----------------------------------------------------------|  
  G----------------------------------------------------------|  
  D----2----4----5----7---5----5--5--------------------------|  
  A----2----4----5----7---5----5--5--------------------------|  
  E----0----2----3----5---3----3--3--------------------------|]  
  *After you have played that a couple of times, fade out on the main*  
  *riff. You should be able to figure out the timing by listening to the*  
  *music.*<!--n:Shit House Shuffle:s:14669:e:1841-->
